# DIAGNOSIS (added for the record):
# Port 5432 was FREE at STEP 0, so the script took the "start fresh" path. But the
# server log has NO entries after 21:01:09 (the previous server's "received fast
# shutdown request" after a Ctrl-C). If the 21:02 server had come up it would have
# logged "database system is ready to accept connections". It did not: the unclean
# shutdown left a stale postmaster.pid, so the new postgres printed "another server
# might be running" and refused to bind. pg_isready then timed out for 60s.
# The "role efebe does not exist" lines are harmless pg_isready probes defaulting to
# the OS username; they do not block readiness. The "server started" text is STALE,
# from an earlier run that used pg_ctl -w.
# FIX (script version 2026-05-30n): before starting, stop any lingering server and
# delete a stale postmaster.pid, then start and poll pg_isready on 127.0.0.1.
